-- Citigroup Said to Hire Nomura's Netherlands Derivative-Sales Head Birkwood
-- Maud Van Gaal
-- 2010-07-12T14:12:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/citigroup-said-to-hire-nomura-s-netherlands-derivative-sales-head-birkwood.html

          
          
             Stephen Birkwood  has left Nomura
Holdings Inc. to join Citigroup Inc. as head of institutional
and retail structured sales for the Netherlands, according to
two people familiar with the matter.  
 Birkwood previously was an executive director and head of
equity derivatives sales for the Netherlands at Nomura in
London, according to one of the people, who declined to be
identified as the move is not official.  
 Felicity Albert , a spokeswoman for Nomura, didnâ€™t
immediately return calls and an e-mail from Bloomberg News 
seeking comment. Attempts to reach Birkwood by phone were 
not successful.  
